        "content": "<p>What's the Mathlib way to write the product of <code>f k</code>, <code>k : Fin n</code>, if the multiplication is noncommutative? In my case, <code>f k</code> are <code>ContinuousLinearMap</code>s. I see at least these options:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Fin.prod#doc\">docs#Fin.prod</a> from Batteries, with virtually no API</li>\n<li><code>(List.finRange n).map f |&gt;.prod</code> which seems too specific</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Did I miss something? Should I add API about <code>Fin.prod</code>, or should I use something else?</p>",
